The cloud is based on the fundamental concept of client-server model. 
Another key principle of cloud computing is that unlike onprem resources, you only pay for what you use
Coud computing can be defined as the on-demand delivery of IT resources over the internet with pay-as-you-go pricing 
Coud deployment types include; Cloud, On-premise and Hybrid deployment. 
Cloud deployment type, you move your resources to the cloud, design and build new applications in the cloud
On-premise deployment type, you have your IT resources deployed on premises using virtulaization and resource management tools
Hybrid cloud deployment type is the combination of both clodud and o_onpremise deployments.
Key benefits of the cloud 
1. Trade fixed expense to variable expense 
2. Benefit from massive economies of scale
3. Stop guesing capacity
4. Speed and agility 
5. Stop spending money to run and maintain data centers 
6. Go global in minutes 
AWS Region: AWS regions are physical locations around the world that contain groups of data centers.
These goups of data ceneters are called availability zones (AZ). Each region contains a minimum of three physically seperated AZ
AZ consist of one or more data centers with redundant power, networking and connectivity 
